n  coverage of saint john common council advocacy for higher taxation of irving oils refinery was notably absent from the newspaper despite extensive coverage in cbc and other news outlets there have also been accusations of irving family political patronage notably involving allan rock and claudette bradshaw of the liberal party of canada incidentsedit the irving whale an oil barge owned by irving oils sister firm jd irving ltd was carrying a cargo of  tons of no  fuel oil for irving oil when it sank in the gulf of st lawrence on september   causing a large initial oil spill and subsequent leaks for the next  years until it was salvaged by the federal government on july   on january    people were killed when an irving oil gas station east of the reversing falls bridge in saint john exploded after a transport truck struck a gas tank on june   william hackett a worker at the irving oil refinery was killed when a pressurized vessel exploded in  a contractor was killed at the irving oil refinery when he fell out of a cherry picker bucket on january   joseph omer allain a construction worker died at the canaport lng facility after falling inside a tank canaport lng is a joint venture between irving oil and repsol see alsoedit kenneth colin irving jd irving limited referencesedit  tapley lance  september  irving lost mining battle but history says canadian corporate giant will not give up pine tree watchdog retrieved  february    house of commons debates official report e cloutier queens printer and controller of stationery    irving oil supports greenhouse treaty new brunswick environmental network cbc news january   archived from the original on july     irving gives unqualified backing to kyoto cbc news retrieved  april    jones robert  june  canaport deals help irving oil earn millions on lng plant cbc news retrieved  december    irving oil plans second refinery for saint john cbc news october   retrieved may     irving shelves nd saint john refinery cbc news july  