velopers cookie statement mobile view irving oil  wikipedia irving oil from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search this article needs additional citations for verification please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed august  learn how and when to remove this template message irving oil ltd type private industry oil and petroleum founded   founder k c irving headquarters saint john new brunswick canada key people james k irving arthur irving john e irving products fuels lubricants petrochemicals parent irving group of companies website wwwirvingoilcom irving oil ltd is a canadian gasoline oil and natural gas producing and exporting company the company is privately owned by arthur irving and his family it is considered part of the irving group of companies irving oil operates the irving oil refinery canadas largest refinery as well as a network of gasoline stations a fleet of oil tankers real estate and other related assets contents  history  refining  distribution  marine  road  rail  retail network  convenience stores  big stops  criticisms  incidents  see also  references  external links historyedit original refinery on the east side of saint john new brunswick capitalist kenneth colin kc irving established irving oil limited in  when he was  years old using gasoline imported by rail the first retailing location was in bouctouche new brunswick irving moved to saint john to open a ford dealership and lubricants plant in  the company expanded across the maritimes through the s to quebec in  newfoundland in  and to maine in  in  irving oil became the first canadian oil company to offer unleaded gasoline at its retail outlets in the late s it became the first oil company in canada and one of the first in north america to offer gasoline with very low sulphur content a fact which was recognized by many automobile manufacturers due to its investment in reducing emissions irving oil was one of the few energy companies in canada to publicly support the kyoto accord refiningedit irving canaport sign old style irving oil station in musquodoboit harbour nova scotia in  the company partnered with standard oil co of california socal to build the irving oil refinery in the east end of saint john irving bought out socals share of the refinery in the late s and expanded the facility to become canadas largest refinery processing over  barrels per day  md in the late s the refinery was upgraded to create some of north americas lowestemission petroleum since  the refinery has been served by the canaport crude oil receiving terminal southeast of saint john in  this facility was expanded to host the canaport lng terminal for importing liquefied natural gas lng irving oil announced in fall  that it had purchased more land near canaport and was examining the feasibility of constructing another barrel  m refinery in the area to complement the original modernized sera refinery in the east end of saint john the new refinery was to be named the eider rock refinery and was to be built under a partnership between irving oil and bp plc on july   both companies announced that they were indefinitely postponing plans to build the second refinery distributionedit this section needs additional citations for verification please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed august  learn how and when to remove this template message marineedit irving oils core retail area is in northeast north america and is well served by a network of regional ports and harbours in atlantic canada quebec and new england  an area that is underserved by pipelines consequently the company economically transports much of its petroleum products to regional distribution terminals at ports throughout the region using its own fleet of coastal tankers in the s irving oil also took delivery of several ultra large crude carriers