n saint john new brunswick after jd irving acquired a tissue paper mill from kimberlyclark in the citys west side adjacent to irving pulp and paper irving began producing tissue for a new subsidiary that was located in moncton nb and was sold under the marketing name majesta in  jd irving opened a tissue converting plant for majesta in dieppe new brunswick that would make use of the tissue produced in saint john irving begins producing private label tissue products and the majesta brand is launched in canada in  irving acquired another tissue paper mill from kimberlyclark as well as a tissue converting plant both located in fort edward new york part of this acquisition saw irving tissue receive the right to market its products under the scotties facial tissue brand in the united states in  jd irving acquired a tissue production and converting plant in toronto from procter  gamble this acquisition saw irving tissue receive the right to market the royale brand in canada in  irving personal care opened a new brunswick plant to produce private label baby diapers and training pants for major north american retailers in  major investments in buildings and a new through air dried paper machine at the irving tissue site in fort edward increases capacity and improves product quality currently irving tissue manufactures products under the majesta and royale brands in canada and the scotties brand in the united states irving tissue is an unsyndicated company referencesedit  a b httpwwwirvingtissuecaaboutaspxidlangtype about irving tissue  a b c d e f httpwwwirvingtissuecapageaspxidekmenselcaffab irving tissue milestones external linksedit official website coordinates °′″n °′″w﻿  ﻿°n °w﻿    v t e irving group of companies subsidiaries irving oil irving oil refinery canaport jd irving ltd irving tissue irving equipment kent building supplies new brunswick railway new brunswick southern railway eastern maine railway maine northern railway brunswick news acadia broadcasting irving